{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e51d1baa-db3e-49ef-9a33-5d6c6724e350","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. Run only the matching test\n2. Automatically re-run it whenever you save a file change\n\nYou can also use the shorter `Name` filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\n`Name=` requires an exact match; `FullyQualifiedName~` does a contains/substring match (useful if you're unsure of the full namespace).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d2220e43-e724-4783-8e3b-4ee69bcaf4fd","outputTokens":159,"requestId":"BC3D:35F104:1E591A7:21B47C8:69FA9923"},"id":"5458fca4-2c89-4804-96ba-d370242df4e4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:28:09.412Z","parentId":"4bbf7285-f177-42e9-9d00-075bec1a3ea8"}
